depositAssetToken(address,uint16,uint256.notice: DEPRECATED: deposits deprecated cTokens tokens as collateral into an account that were listed prior to the migration to prime cash. Future listed tokens will not have asset tokens and will revert in this method.

params.amountExternalPrecision: the amount of asset tokens in its native decimal precision (i.e. 8 decimals for cTokens).
params.currencyId: currency id of the asset token

returns._0: asset tokens minted and deposited to the account in internal decimals (8)

depositUnderlyingToken(address,uint16,ui.notice: Deposits and wraps the underlying token for a particular cToken. Does not settle assets or check free collateral, idea is to be as gas efficient as possible during potential liquidation events.

params.amountExternalPrecision: the amount of underlying tokens in its native decimal precision (i.e. 18 decimals for DAI or 6 decimals for USDC). This will be converted to 8 decimals during transfer.
params.currencyId: currency id of the asset token that wraps this underlying

returns._0: asset tokens minted and deposited to the account in internal decimals (8)

enableBitmapCurrency(uint16).notice: Enables a bitmap currency for msg.sender, account cannot have any assets when this call occurs. Will revert if the account already has a bitmap currency set.

params.currencyId: the currency to enable the bitmap for.

enablePrimeBorrow(bool).notice: A per account setting that allows it to borrow prime cash (i.e. incur negative cash) as a result of account initiated actions. Accounts can still incur negative cash as a result of fCash settlement regardless of this setting.

params.allowPrimeBorrow: true if the account can borrow prime cash

getLibInfo().notice: Get a list of deployed library addresses (sorted by library name)

nTokenRedeem(address,uint16,uint96,bool,.notice: Allows accounts to redeem nTokens into constituent assets and then absorb the assets into their portfolio. Due to the complexity here, it is not allowed to be called during a batch trading operation and must be done separately.

params.acceptResidualAssets: if true, will place any residual fCash that could not be sold (either due to slippage or because it was idiosyncratic) into the account's portfolio
params.redeemer: the address that holds the nTokens to redeem
params.sellTokenAssets: attempt to sell residual fCash and convert to cash
params.tokensToRedeem_: the amount of nTokens to convert to cash

returns._0: total amount of asset cash redeemed
returns._1: true or false if there were residuals that were placed into the portfolio

settleAccount(address).notice: Method for manually settling an account, generally should not be called because other methods will check if an account needs to be settled automatically. If a bitmap account has debt and is settled via this method, the hasDebt flag will not be cleared until a free collateral check is performed on the account.

returns._0: returns true if account has been settled

withdraw(uint16,uint88,bool).notice: Withdraws balances from Notional, may also redeem to underlying tokens on user request. Will settle and do free collateral checks if required. Can only be called by msg.sender, operators who want to withdraw for an account must do an authenticated call via ERC1155Action `safeTransferFrom` or `safeBatchTransferFrom`

params.amountInternalPrecision: the amount of cash balance in internal 8 decimal precision to withdraw, this is be denominated in prime cash. If set to uint88 max, will withdraw an entire cash balance.
params.currencyId: currency id of the asset token
